## Web Research Complete

**Queries**: 4 searches executed + 1 page fetch
**Sources**: 5 relevant sources found
**Artifact**: `/home/asiri/.archon/workspaces/alexsiri7/reli/artifacts/runs/1bdaabf2839573ff2f1331b904f1bb83/web-research.md`

### Key Findings

- **Root cause confirmed**: `ssh-keyscan` runs immediately after Tailscale connects, but Tailscale signals "ready" before peer routing is fully established. The host at `100.120.193.82` is unreachable for a window of 10–60 seconds post-connect.
- **Well-known issue**: [tailscale/github-action#109](https://github.com/tailscale/github-action/issues/109) documents the exact same failure. Community-confirmed fix is `sleep 30` before keyscan; a retry loop is more robust.
- **Both jobs affected**: The `Setup SSH key` step is duplicated verbatim in `deploy-staging` (lines 37–46) and `deploy-production` (lines 137–146) of `.github/workflows/staging-pipeline.yml`.
- **Fix**: Replace the single `ssh-keyscan` call with a retry loop (10 attempts × 10s sleep = 100s max) or add `sleep 30` before the scan.

### Gaps

- Cannot confirm whether the server's SSH daemon itself was also down; the retry loop will surface that as a distinct failure if so.

Sources:
- [Failed to ssh-keyscan to tailscaled dns after tailscale/github-action@main · Issue #109](https://github.com/tailscale/github-action/issues/109)
- [Add retry behaviour when ssh-keyscan returns nothing · Issue #281 · buildkite/agent](https://github.com/buildkite/agent/issues/281)
- [Github Action getting tailscale version · Issue #147 · tailscale/github-action](https://github.com/tailscale/github-action/issues/147)
- [How to Retry a Failed Command in Shell | Baeldung on Linux](https://www.baeldung.com/linux/shell-retry-failed-command)
