**Summary of findings for PR #683** (`fix: add retry loop and timeout to ssh-keyscan in deploy pipeline`):

**Verdict: APPROVE** — the overall error handling structure is correct (bounded retries, hard fail on exhaustion, explicit error message). Two minor issues found:

| # | Severity | Issue | Fix |
|---|----------|-------|-----|
| 1 | MEDIUM | `ssh-keyscan 2>/dev/null` silences stderr on every attempt — non-timeout failures (DNS, ECONNREFUSED, ACL block) leave no diagnostic trace | Remove `2>/dev/null` so errors stream to the Actions log |
| 2 | LOW | `sleep 5` and "retrying in 5s..." run on the 5th (final) iteration — misleading message, 5s wasted on every fully-failed run | Guard with `[ "$i" -lt 5 ]` |

Neither issue is blocking. The retry structure, timeout increase (`-T 30`), and outer guard check are all solid.
